WHICH, OF COURSE,

18:59.138 --> 19:01.099
COULD ONLY MEAN...

19:01.140 --> 19:02.767
TRINIDAD.

19:02.809 --> 19:06.186
WHAT ABOUT THE BEAN?

19:02.809 --> 19:06.186
TRINITARIO? FORASTERO?

19:06.228 --> 19:07.480
NEITHER.

19:07.521 --> 19:08.982
THIS COULD ONLY BE

19:07.521 --> 19:08.982
THE CRIOLLO BEAN,

19:09.023 --> 19:10.900
UNLIKE THAT THING YOU PUT

19:09.023 --> 19:10.900
IN YOUR MOUTH, LAVERNE,

19:10.942 --> 19:12.735
WHICH I COULD SMELL FROM HERE,

19:10.942 --> 19:12.735
WAS AN ARRIBA,

19:12.777 --> 19:15.154
THE MOST OVERRATED BEAN

19:12.777 --> 19:15.154
IN THE WORLD,

19:15.195 --> 19:17.364
THE ONE YOU CALLED

19:15.195 --> 19:17.364
"OUTSTANDING."

19:17.406 --> 19:20.409
OH, AND...

19:20.451 --> 19:22.369
JUST UNDER 85%.

19:22.411 --> 19:25.289
WHOA, WHOA, AND WHOA!

19:25.331 --> 19:28.501
84%!

19:28.542 --> 19:31.087
LET'S HEAR IT

19:28.542 --> 19:31.087
FOR THE CHOCOLATE WHISPERER,

19:31.129 --> 19:33.172
CLARISSA DuBOIS!

19:33.213 --> 19:34.381
[ APPLAUSE ]

19:35.591 --> 19:37.718
JUST FROM A PIECE OF CHOCOLATE?

19:37.760 --> 19:38.886
THAT'S MY GIRL.

19:38.928 --> 19:40.638
SHE'S SCARY.

19:40.680 --> 19:42.389
[ SNIFFLES ]

19:42.431 --> 19:45.018
WOW. LOOK AT THAT.

19:42.431 --> 19:45.018
ISN'T THAT SOMETHING?

19:45.059 --> 19:47.728
MS. DuBOIS,

19:45.059 --> 19:47.728
THAT WAS VERY IMPRESSIVE.

19:47.770 --> 19:48.729
WELL, I DIDN'T MEAN

19:47.770 --> 19:48.729
TO MAKE LAVERNE CRY.

19:48.771 --> 19:50.356
MY NAME'S GREG SHERMAN.

19:50.397 --> 19:51.649
-I'M WORKING WITH --

19:50.397 --> 19:51.649
-EXCUSE US, CRAIG.

19:50.397 --> 19:51.649
WE HAVE A MEETING.

19:51.691 --> 19:53.609
IT'S GREG, THE MAKO.

19:53.651 --> 19:56.904
[ CONVERSING IN CHINESE ]

19:56.946 --> 19:58.238
TELL ME WHAT THEY'RE SAYING.

19:58.280 --> 19:59.657
"IT'S OUR HONOR, MS. DuBOIS.

19:59.699 --> 20:03.953
HONG KONG AND SHANGHAI,

19:59.699 --> 20:03.953
THEY'RE READY."

20:05.454 --> 20:09.750
"YOUR CAFES WILL BE

20:05.454 --> 20:09.750
THE STARBUCKS OF CHOCOLATE."

20:09.792 --> 20:11.919
SHE'S OPENING CHOCOLATE CAFES

20:09.792 --> 20:11.919
IN CHINA?

20:11.961 --> 20:13.087
That's why that idiot

20:13.129 --> 20:15.173
Count Chocula

20:13.129 --> 20:15.173
is buying cocoa futures.

20:15.214 --> 20:16.590
Demand is gonna skyrocket.

20:16.632 --> 20:18.885
"THAT IS A NICE DRESS

20:16.632 --> 20:18.885
YOU'RE WEARING."

20:18.926 --> 20:21.303
JUST THE RELEVANT STUFF.

20:21.345 --> 20:26.517
"88 THIS YEAR,

20:21.345 --> 20:26.517
120 IN THE NEXT TWO YEARS."

20:34.233 --> 20:36.777
WE NEED TO TALK.

20:36.819 --> 20:38.445
I HAVE NOTHING TO SAY TO YOU.

20:39.405 --> 20:41.574
[ CAR ALARM CHIRPS ]

20:54.879 --> 20:57.339
I GAVE YOU THE CHANCE

20:54.879 --> 20:57.339
TO DO THIS EASY.

20:57.381 --> 20:58.549
YOU PASSED.

20:58.591 --> 21:01.177
[ SIGHS ]

21:01.219 --> 21:03.096
I KNOW ABOUT CHINA.

21:03.137 --> 21:04.597
NATE, ELIOT'S IN POSITION.

21:04.638 --> 21:05.973
JUST SAY THE WORD, NATE,

21:06.015 --> 21:08.226
AND I'LL COME IN THERE

21:06.015 --> 21:08.226
AND TEAR THEIR LUNGS OUT.

21:08.267 --> 21:10.728
NOT NECESSARY.

21:10.770 --> 21:14.523
OH, IT'S NECESSARY, ALL RIGHT.

21:14.565 --> 21:16.859
YOUR WHOLE PLAN DEPENDS ON IT.

21:16.901 --> 21:19.862
200 NOUVEAU RICHE

21:16.901 --> 21:19.862
CHOCOLATE CAFES

21:19.904 --> 21:22.115
WHERE A BILLION CHINESE

21:19.904 --> 21:22.115
CONSUME LESS CHOCOLATE

21:22.156 --> 21:23.323
THAN 7 MILLION SWISS?

21:23.365 --> 21:26.994
THAT'S LIKE GOING LONG ON DVDs

21:23.365 --> 21:26.994
IN 1994.

21:27.036 --> 21:29.830
SO NOW YOU KNOW WHY

21:27.036 --> 21:29.830
I HIRED HARDISON.

21:29.872 --> 21:31.874
WELL, THAT'S WHAT YOU

21:29.872 --> 21:31.874
WANT ME TO THINK.

21:31.916 --> 21:32.959
[ CHUCKLES ]

21:33.000 --> 21:34.376
BUT YOU CAN'T RUN A GRIFT

21:33.000 --> 21:34.376
ON THE MAKO.

21:34.418 --> 21:37.046
WHO'S THE MAKO?

21:37.088 --> 21:40.007
I'M  THE MAKO...

21:40.049 --> 21:42.176
AND I WANT TO KNOW

21:40.049 --> 21:42.176
WHAT THE ACTION IS,

21:42.218 --> 21:45.012
OR MY MAN HERE IS GONNA GO

21:42.218 --> 21:45.012
PASO DOBLE ON YOUR SKULL.

21:46.973 --> 21:51.227
THE, UH -- THE CROP REPORT

21:46.973 --> 21:51.227
IS GONNA COME OUT ON FRIDAY.

21:51.269 --> 21:53.687
IT'S GONNA SAY THAT SUPPLY

21:51.269 --> 21:53.687
IS NORMAL, AVERAGE.

21:53.729 --> 21:55.856
YES, BUT DEMAND IS GONNA JUMP.

21:55.898 --> 21:58.525
NO, NO.

21:55.898 --> 21:58.525
THE CROP REPORT IS WRONG.

21:58.567 --> 22:01.528
WHO TOLD YOU THIS,

21:58.567 --> 22:01.528
YOUR CHOCOLATE WHISPERER?

22:01.570 --> 22:04.323
NO, NO. SHE'S LEGIT.

22:01.570 --> 22:04.323
SHE HAS NOTHING TO DO WITH THIS.

22:04.364 --> 22:05.908
[ CHUCKLES ]

22:04.364 --> 22:05.908
THAT'S FUNNY,

22:05.950 --> 22:08.035
'CAUSE YOU'RE SLEEPING WITH HER.

22:09.829 --> 22:11.413
I SEE IT.

22:11.455 --> 22:13.332
IT'S IN YOUR BODY LANGUAGE

22:11.455 --> 22:13.332
WHEN YOU'RE TOGETHER.

22:13.373 --> 22:14.917
IT'S IN YOUR EYES

22:13.373 --> 22:14.917
WHEN YOU LOOK AT HER.

22:14.959 --> 22:16.376
YOU TWO HAVE

22:14.959 --> 22:16.376
A CARNAL RELATIONSHIP.

22:16.418 --> 22:18.504
SEE, HE -- HE -- HE'S JUST

22:16.418 --> 22:18.504
TRYING TO RATTLE NATE.

22:18.545 --> 22:21.174
YOU  DID  SAY HE READS PEOPLE

22:18.545 --> 22:21.174
BETTER THAN ANYONE YOU KNOW.

22:21.215 --> 22:22.549
Y'ALL NASTY.

22:22.591 --> 22:24.551
I...

22:24.593 --> 22:25.719
LISTEN TO ME.

22:24.593 --> 22:25.719
IT'S NOT HER, OKAY?

22:25.761 --> 22:28.181
-I HAVE A GUY.

22:25.761 --> 22:28.181
-A GUY IN THE C.F.T.C.?

22:28.222 --> 22:31.309
NO. IT'S -- IT'S A GUY WHO...

22:28.222 --> 22:31.309
KNOWS THINGS.

22:31.349 --> 22:33.144
WHEN THE CROP REPORT COMES OUT,

22:33.186 --> 22:36.230
EVERYONE'S GONNA THINK

22:33.186 --> 22:36.230
IT'S BUSINESS AS USUAL.

22:36.272 --> 22:37.815
I CONTINUE BUYING FUTURES.

22:37.857 --> 22:39.233
THEN, IN A MONTH OR SO,

22:39.275 --> 22:41.902
THE WORLD FINDS OUT

22:39.275 --> 22:41.902
SUPPLY IS IN THE TOILET.

22:41.944 --> 22:43.779
THAT'S WHEN I,

22:41.944 --> 22:43.779
WITH CONTROLLING INTEREST

22:43.821 --> 22:45.906
IN NEARLY ALL COCOA FUTURES,

22:43.821 --> 22:45.906
ANNOUNCE CHINA.

22:45.948 --> 22:49.576
YOU'RE TALKING 100 MILLION.

22:53.122 --> 22:54.248
HOW'S THAT?

22:54.290 --> 22:55.541
-YEAH.

22:54.290 --> 22:55.541
-OKAY.

22:55.582 --> 22:57.001
WHY DIDN'T YOU SAY ANYTHING?

22:57.043 --> 22:58.919
PARKER.

22:58.961 --> 23:00.254
HEY, NATE,

22:58.961 --> 23:00.254
SHE'S JUST SAYING, MAN.

23:00.296 --> 23:01.797
LOOK, WE'LL DISCUSS IT LATER.

23:01.839 --> 23:04.091
OKAY, RIGHT NOW WE'VE GOT

23:01.839 --> 23:04.091
TO WORRY ABOUT SHERMAN.

23:04.133 --> 23:05.301
HE'S CLEVER.

23:05.343 --> 23:06.927
HE'S TOO CLEVER TO FALL

23:05.343 --> 23:06.927
FOR THE BIG STORE.

23:06.969 --> 23:09.138
HE KNOWS EVERY SHILL,

23:06.969 --> 23:09.138
EVERY PLAYER IN THE COUNTRY.

23:09.180 --> 23:10.597
WE'VE GOT NOBODY WE CAN CALL.

23:10.639 --> 23:13.184
THAT'S WHY

23:10.639 --> 23:13.184
WE'RE GONNA USE CIVILIANS.

23:13.226 --> 23:14.352
TRUST ME.

23:14.392 --> 23:15.602
WE GOT THE GUY ON THE DANGLE.

23:15.644 --> 23:17.021
HE'S JUST ABOUT TO BITE.

23:17.063 --> 23:18.898
WE JUST GOT TO KEEP HIM

23:17.063 --> 23:18.898
OFF BALANCE

23:18.939 --> 23:20.983
AND JUST KEEP PUSHING HIM

23:18.939 --> 23:20.983
AND PUSHING HIM

23:21.025 --> 23:22.860
UNTIL HE'S OUT

23:21.025 --> 23:22.860
OF HIS COMFORT ZONE.

23:22.902 --> 23:25.905
HOW FAR OUT

23:22.902 --> 23:25.905
YOU TRYING TO PUSH HIM?

23:33.871 --> 23:35.873
[ BIRDS CALLING ]

23:39.168 --> 23:41.128
NATE, HOW MANY MONITORS

23:39.168 --> 23:41.128
DO WE NEED?

23:41.170 --> 23:43.047
As many as you can.

23:47.885 --> 23:49.929
WOW!

23:49.970 --> 23:51.222
YOU'VE ACTUALLY DONE

23:49.970 --> 23:51.222
SOME ACTING.

23:51.264 --> 23:53.891
OH, YES.

23:51.264 --> 23:53.891
I PERFORMED "EQUUS."

23:53.933 --> 23:55.475
THEATER IN THE ROUND.

23:55.517 --> 23:57.644
I LOVE THAT PLAY.

23:55.517 --> 23:57.644
IT'S ONE OF MY --

23:57.686 --> 23:59.563
WHO DID YOU PLAY,

23:57.686 --> 23:59.563
ALAN OR -- OR DR. DYSART?

23:59.605 --> 24:01.399
I WAS NUGGET.

24:02.691 --> 24:03.650
THE HORSE?

24:03.692 --> 24:05.027
YES.

24:05.069 --> 24:06.486
BUT I WAS THE FRONT END.

24:07.863 --> 24:10.699
GO OVER TO THE OTHER SIDE,

24:07.863 --> 24:10.699
THEN UNLOAD WHAT'S IN THERE.

24:10.741 --> 24:12.368
THEN THAT IS THE THING --

24:10.741 --> 24:12.368
YEAH?

24:12.410 --> 24:13.619
MR. FORD.

24:13.660 --> 24:15.246
YES, MS...?

24:15.288 --> 24:16.830
COX, WITH AN "X."

24:16.872 --> 24:18.498
OF COURSE.

24:18.540 --> 24:20.084
YEAH, THAT SOPHIE WOMAN --

24:20.126 --> 24:22.836
I DON'T THINK HER CRACKERS

24:20.126 --> 24:22.836
ARE QUITE TOASTED.

24:22.878 --> 24:25.172
SHE WANTS ME TO MOONWALK

24:22.878 --> 24:25.172
WITH A BEAR.

24:25.214 --> 24:27.591
NO, NO. SEE, WE'RE DOING A

24:25.214 --> 24:27.591
VERSION OF THE MOONWALKING BEAR.

24:27.633 --> 24:31.262
I.B.,

24:27.633 --> 24:31.262
INATTENTIONAL BLINDNESS.

24:31.304 --> 24:32.430
BASICALLY, WHAT IT IS,

24:32.470 --> 24:34.556
IS IF A PERSON IS SO FOCUSED

24:32.470 --> 24:34.556
ON SOMETHING

24:34.598 --> 24:36.183
THAT, YOU KNOW, THEY DON'T --

24:36.225 --> 24:39.019
THEY CAN'T SEE THE OBVIOUS THING

24:36.225 --> 24:39.019
RIGHT IN FRONT OF THEM,

24:39.061 --> 24:41.397
LIKE --

24:39.061 --> 24:41.397
LIKE A MOONWALKING BEAR.

24:41.439 --> 24:43.690
BUT WHAT IF THE BEAR EATS ME?

24:45.483 --> 24:47.194
CAN WE --

24:45.483 --> 24:47.194
CAN WE JUST STOP A MINUTE?

24:47.236 --> 24:49.155
IN THE BUSH, YOU STOP MOVING,

24:47.236 --> 24:49.155
YOU DIE.

24:49.196 --> 24:50.614
LIKE A -- LIKE A SHARK!

24:50.656 --> 24:53.075
THAT'S WHAT THEY CALL ME,

24:50.656 --> 24:53.075
"THE MAKO."

24:54.201 --> 24:56.036
ARE YOU MAKING FUN OF ME?

24:56.078 --> 24:57.997
NO. NO.

24:58.038 --> 25:00.291
NO, IT'S MY NICKNAME,

24:58.038 --> 25:00.291
MY MONIKER.

25:00.333 --> 25:02.084
ALL THE GREATS HAD ONE.

25:03.585 --> 25:05.754
GREAT WHAT?

25:05.796 --> 25:07.631
NEVER MIND. LOOK --

25:07.673 --> 25:10.009
SO YOU WORK

25:07.673 --> 25:10.009
FOR THIS COUNT CHOCULA.

25:10.050 --> 25:11.551
I DON'T WORK FOR ANYBODY.

25:11.593 --> 25:14.263
YEAH, BUT HE HIRED YOU

25:11.593 --> 25:14.263
TO TAKE ME OUT HERE

25:14.305 --> 25:16.223
AND SHOW ME THE COCOA FIELDS.

25:16.265 --> 25:18.392
IT'S NOT ABOUT THE COCOA FIELDS.

25:18.434 --> 25:19.726
IT'S ABOUT THE NATURE.

25:19.768 --> 25:21.895
NATURE, YEAH.

25:21.937 --> 25:23.730
ALL RIGHT.

25:21.937 --> 25:23.730
NOT "NATURE."

25:23.772 --> 25:24.982
"THE  NATURE."

25:25.024 --> 25:26.942
THE NATURE OF A MAN.

25:29.569 --> 25:31.613
THE NATURE OF DARKNESS.

25:35.284 --> 25:37.370
AAH!

25:37.411 --> 25:38.162
[ SNAKE HISSES ]

25:38.204 --> 25:39.830
SEE THE SNAKE?

25:39.872 --> 25:41.415
[ HISSING STOPS,

25:39.872 --> 25:41.415
SQUISHING ]

25:45.961 --> 25:50.299
YOU EAT A SNAKE HEART,

25:45.961 --> 25:50.299
YOU CONSUME ITS SOUL.

25:54.803 --> 25:58.556
[ GRUNTS ] OKAY. ALL RIGHT.

25:54.803 --> 25:58.556
THAT'S MORE LIKE IT.

25:58.598 --> 26:00.558
WHERE'D YOU GET ALL THESE,

25:58.598 --> 26:00.558
PARKER?

26:00.600 --> 26:01.559
HUH?

26:01.601 --> 26:03.145
YOU KNOW.

26:04.522 --> 26:06.399
Put it back, Parker.

26:15.032 --> 26:16.700
UH, HARDISON, WHAT DO YOU GOT?

26:16.742 --> 26:17.826
NOTHING YET, NATE.

26:17.868 --> 26:19.661
I MIGHT HAVE TO CHANGE LOCATIONS

26:19.703 --> 26:21.830
TO MAKE SURE I GET IT

26:19.703 --> 26:21.830
IN REAL TIME.

26:21.872 --> 26:23.207
Well, do what you got to do.

26:31.631 --> 26:33.759
THOSE ARE

26:31.631 --> 26:33.759
THE TOP-PRODUCING COCOA FIELDS

26:33.800 --> 26:34.885
ON THE ENTIRE CONTINENT.

26:34.927 --> 26:37.179
SO? THEY'RE JUST

26:34.927 --> 26:37.179
MOWING DOWN TREES.

26:37.221 --> 26:41.641
DO YOU KNOW WHAT THE MOST

26:37.221 --> 26:41.641
DANGEROUS THING IS TO COCOA?

26:41.683 --> 26:43.060
SUNLIGHT.

26:43.102 --> 26:45.229
TOO MUCH SUN,

26:43.102 --> 26:45.229
AND THE CROPS WON'T YIELD.

26:45.271 --> 26:47.565
WELL, THERE ARE THOUSANDS

26:45.271 --> 26:47.565
OF ACRES OF COCOA.

26:47.647 --> 26:50.150
THE FARMERS ARE NOT GONNA

26:47.647 --> 26:50.150
CUT DOWN ALL THE TREES.

26:50.192 --> 26:54.280
THOSE AREN'T FARMERS.

26:50.192 --> 26:54.280
THAT'S THE LOCAL GOVERNMENT.

26:54.321 --> 26:56.865
THEY'RE IN THE TIMBERS BUSINESS.

26:56.907 --> 26:59.701
THEY'RE CUTTING DOWN EVERY TREE

26:56.907 --> 26:59.701
IN THE SQUARE 100-MILE RADIUS.

26:59.743 --> 27:01.078
OFF THE RECORD.

27:01.120 --> 27:04.831
THAT'S WHY HE KNOWS

27:01.120 --> 27:04.831
THE CROP REPORT WILL BE WRONG.

27:04.873 --> 27:07.460
THEY DON'T KNOW.

27:11.547 --> 27:13.340
YOU TWO, GO LONG ON TIMBER,

27:13.382 --> 27:16.260
100,000 SHARES,

27:13.382 --> 27:16.260
AT LEAST TWO DOZEN ACCOUNTS.

27:16.302 --> 27:19.012
THE REST OF YOU,

27:16.302 --> 27:19.012
STAY ON THE FLOOD.

27:19.054 --> 27:22.182
EVERY NETWORK --

27:19.054 --> 27:22.182
FINANCIAL, SOCIAL MEDIA --

27:22.224 --> 27:25.561
I WANT IT TO BE LIKE

27:22.224 --> 27:25.561
WHEN NOAH BUILT HIS BOAT!

27:27.271 --> 27:30.983
I CANNOT WAIT TO MAKE THIS CALL.

27:31.024 --> 27:32.318
I'M STILL NOT SURE.

27:32.359 --> 27:34.027
SHANNON'S BEEN DOING THIS

27:32.359 --> 27:34.027
A LOT LONGER THAN I HAVE.

27:34.069 --> 27:35.737
NO, LISTEN, IT'S WORKING.

27:34.069 --> 27:35.737
HE'S HOOKED.

27:35.779 --> 27:37.531
HARDISON'S BEEN MONITORING

27:35.779 --> 27:37.531
HIS ACCOUNTS.

27:37.573 --> 27:38.865
SAID HE WENT LONG ON TIMBER.

27:38.907 --> 27:40.159
HARDISON FOUND HIS MONEY?

27:40.200 --> 27:42.035
WELL, THOSE BUYS WERE

27:40.200 --> 27:42.035
FROM THE COMPANY ACCOUNT,

27:42.077 --> 27:43.996
BUT HE'S GONNA HAVE TO GO

27:42.077 --> 27:43.996
INTO HIS PERSONALS

27:44.037 --> 27:46.373
IF HE WANTS TO GET ENOUGH CASH

27:44.037 --> 27:46.373
TO GO INTO THE BIG STORE.

27:46.415 --> 27:47.749
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

27:47.791 --> 27:49.293
OH.

27:51.587 --> 27:53.255
HMM.

27:53.297 --> 27:54.465
YEAH.

27:54.507 --> 27:55.924
IT'S THE MAKO.

27:55.966 --> 27:57.009
THE WHAT?

27:57.050 --> 27:59.219
GREG SHERMAN.

27:59.261 --> 28:00.720
OH. OH, YEAH.

28:00.762 --> 28:02.806
I WANT IN.

28:02.848 --> 28:05.058
LISTEN, THE PAYOUT IS "BOXCAR,"

28:02.848 --> 28:05.058
ALL RIGHT?

28:05.100 --> 28:07.853
IF YOU WANT A PIECE OF THIS,

28:05.100 --> 28:07.853
IT'S $10 MILLION IN CASH.

28:07.894 --> 28:09.104
WHEN DO YOU NEED IT?

28:09.146 --> 28:10.939
WELL, THE CROP REPORT COMES OUT

28:09.146 --> 28:10.939
IN 12 HOURS,

28:10.981 --> 28:12.566
SO, UH, YOU KNOW,

28:10.981 --> 28:12.566
I'LL NEED THE CASH

28:12.608 --> 28:13.567
ON MY TRADING-ROOM FLOOR

28:13.609 --> 28:15.152
IF YOU WANT TO BE

28:13.609 --> 28:15.152
A PART OF THIS.

28:15.194 --> 28:17.613
OTHERWISE, I'M GONNA HAVE TO,

28:15.194 --> 28:17.613
YOU KNOW, MOVE ON WITHOUT YOU.

28:19.865 --> 28:22.493
I'M IN.

28:22.535 --> 28:24.203
[ BEEP ]

28:24.244 --> 28:26.246
HE'S IN.

28:31.001 --> 28:33.546
OKAY. WE'RE GONNA RUN IT AGAIN.

28:33.587 --> 28:35.464
ALL RIGHT. EVERYBODY...

28:35.506 --> 28:37.216
PLACES. BACK TO ONE!

28:37.257 --> 28:38.842
ALL RIGHT. YEAH.

28:37.257 --> 28:38.842
GO BACK TO YOUR PLACE.

28:38.884 --> 28:40.469
THIS -- THIS IS A DISASTER.

28:40.511 --> 28:42.638
WELL, MAYBE WE'LL GET LUCKY

28:40.511 --> 28:42.638
AND HE WON'T SHOW UP.

28:42.680 --> 28:43.930
OH, HE'S GONNA SHOW.

28:43.972 --> 28:45.891
OKAY, PEOPLE. ONCE AGAIN.

28:45.932 --> 28:49.687
PARKER, LOVELY BLONDE HERE,

28:45.932 --> 28:49.687
IS GREG SHERMAN.

28:49.728 --> 28:51.271
-BOO!

28:51.313 --> 28:53.899
ELIOT IS HIS DRIVER.

28:53.940 --> 28:55.568
NOW, ONCE THEY'VE ENTERED,

28:55.609 --> 28:57.944
IT'S TOO LATE

28:55.609 --> 28:57.944
TO BEGIN YOUR MOVES.

28:57.986 --> 28:59.613
YOU NEED TO BE MOVING

28:59.655 --> 29:01.490
AND DOING EVERYTHING THAT

28:59.655 --> 29:01.490
YOU'RE DOING  BEFORE  THEY ENTER.

29:01.532 --> 29:02.575
BEFORE.

